<title>
ECT Sensor Inspection
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENAP70B1306011">ECT Sensor Removal and Installation</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
There is a possibility of causing short circuit, corrosion and loose connection of terminal when wet terminal is connected.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
Do not measure resistance with terminal of the ECT sensor soaked in water. As for the measurement in the soaked state, an accurate measurement cannot be done.
</ptxt>
</attention3>
<ptxt>
Check resistance between terminal “1” and terminal “2” varies depending on engine coolant temperature as shown in graph below.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If faulty condition is found, replace thermostat case assembly (1). 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B1606008"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
